$PAR
True or false:
Let \(\lbrace x_n \rbrace_{n=1}^\infty\) be a bounded sequence.
Then for every \(x\) such that
\(\liminf \, x_n \leq x \leq \limsup \, x_n ,\) there
exists a subsequence
\(\lbrace x_{n_k} \rbrace_{k=1}^\infty\) converging to \(x.\)
$BR
END_TEXT
